metadata:
  section_id: 56
  section_name: Chapter 56
  hadith_first: 392
  hadith_last: 402

hadiths[11]{hadithnumber,text,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro}:
392,"“If someone sees me in his sleep, he has indeed seen me, for Satan cannot imitate me!""",,,49107,"'Abdullah ibn Mas'ud, that the Prophet said (Allah bless him and give him peace):",Chapter 56
393,"“Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace): ‘If someone sees me in his sleep, he has indeed seen me, for Satan cannot appear in disguise as me’(or: ‘cannot imitate me’).”",,,49108,"Abu Huraira (may Allah be well pleased with him) said:",Chapter 56
394,"""Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace): “If someone sees me in his sleep, he has indeed seen me!”",,,49109,"Abu Malik al-Ashja'i reported that his father said:",Chapter 56
395,"“I saw Amr ibn Huraith, the Companion of the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace), when I was a little boy.”",,,49110,"Khalaf ibn Khalifa said:",Chapter 56
396,"“Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) said: ‘If someone sees me in his sleep, he has indeed seen me, for Satan cannot imitate me!’ The father then related this to Ibn Abbas, saying that he had seen the Prophet. He also mentioned al-Hasan ibn ‘Ali, noting that he resembled the Prophet. To this Ibn 'Abbas replied, ‘Yes, he resembled him.’”",,,49111,"'Asim ibn Kulaib’s father heard Abu Huraira say:",Chapter 56
397,"“I saw the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) in my sleep in the time of Ibn 'Abbas, so I said to Ibn 'Abbas:\n‘I saw Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) in my sleep!’\nIbn 'Abbas said: “Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) used to say: ‘Satan cannot imitate me, so if someone sees me in his sleep, he has indeed seen me!’ Can you describe this man whom you saw in your sleep?” “Yes,” he said. “I shall describe for you an average man: his body and his flesh were brown-to-white; he was black eyed, endowed with a pleasant smile and handsome facial features; his beard went from here to here, and it came down over the top of his chest.”\n'Awf said: ""I do not know what could be added to this description,” and Ibn 'Abbas said: ""If you had seen him in the state of wakefulness, you could not have described him more accurately than this.”",,,49112,"Yazid al-Farisi, who used to inscribe copies of the Qur’an said:",Chapter 56
398,"""I am older then Qatadah.""",,,49113,"(Regarding one of the narrators of the previous narration) `Awf (Abu Jamilah) al-A`rabi said:",Chapter 56
399,"“Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace): ‘If someone sees me (meaning in his sleep), he has seen me truly!'”",,,49114,"Abu Qatada said:",Chapter 56
400,"""The Prophet said (Allah bless him and give him peace): 'If someone sees me in his sleep, he has indeed seen me, for Satan cannot impersonate me!' He also said: 'The vision of the believer is one of forty-six parts of Prophethood.'""",,,49115,"Anas said:",Chapter 56
401,"“If you are afflicted with the responsibility of judgeship, you must follow the !”",,,49116,"Abdu llah ibn al-Mubarak said:",Chapter 56
402,"""This tradition  is religion, so consider from whom you accept your religion.”",,,49117,"Ibn Sirin said:",Chapter 56
